This paper deals with the problem of multi-person pose tracking in videos using a probabilistic neural pose predictor and Sequential Monte Carlo (SMC) method. The paper proposes a novel approach that utilizes uncertainty-aware modeling and a recurrent architecture to handle difficult situations. The paper's focus on computer vision and machine learning techniques suggests that it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of probabilistic modeling and neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The use of a recurrent architecture suggests that it could also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the use of video data suggests that it could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
